def solution(stdin: str) -> str:
    n = int(stdin.readline())
    lines = [tuple(map(int, line.split())) for line in stdin.readlines()]
    lines.sort()
    points = set()
    for i in range(n):
        for j in range(i + 1, n):
            if lines[i][0] == lines[j][0] or lines[i][1] == lines[j][1] or lines[i][2] == lines[j][2] or lines[i][3] == lines[j][3]:
                points.add(lines[i][0])
                points.add(lines[i][1])
                points.add(lines[i][2])
                points.add(lines[i][3])
                points.add(lines[j][0])
                points.add(lines[j][1])
                points.add(lines[j][2])
                points.add(lines[j][3])
    return str(len(points))

def solution(stdin: str) -> str:
    n = int(stdin.readline())
    rooms = [int(stdin.readline()) for _ in range(n)]
    rooms.sort()
    min_dist = rooms[-1] - rooms[0]
    for i in range(1, n):
        dist = rooms[i] - rooms[i - 1]
        if dist < min_dist:
            min_dist = dist
            close_room = rooms[i - 1]
            open_room = rooms[i]
    return f'{min_dist}\n{close_room}\n{open_room}'

    return str(ans)

def solution(stdin: str) -> str:
    n = int(stdin.readline())
    jaap = [int(x) for x in stdin.readline().split()]
    jan = [int(x) for x in stdin.readline().split()]
    thijs = [int(x) for x in stdin.readline().split()]
    
    jaap_order = [0] * n
    jan_order = [0] * n
    thijs_order = [0] * n
    
    for i in range(n):
        jaap_order[jaap[i] - 1] = i + 1
        jan_order[jan[i] - 1] = i + 1
        thijs_order[thijs[i] - 1] = i + 1
    
    jaap_pairs = 0
    jan_pairs = 0
    thijs_pairs = 0
    
    for i in range(n):
        if jaap_order[i] == i + 1:
            jaap_pairs += 1
        if jan_order[i] == i + 1:
            jan_pairs += 1
        if thijs_order[i] == i + 1:
            thijs_pairs += 1
    
    return str(jaap_pairs * jan_pairs * thijs_pairs)

def solution(stdin: str) -> str:
    n = int(stdin.readline().strip())
    bottles = [int(x) for x in stdin.readline().strip().split()]
    t = int(stdin.readline().strip())
    bottles.sort()
    bottles.reverse()
    if t > sum(bottles):
        return "impossible"
    moves = []
    while t > 0:
        if bottles[0] > t:
            moves.append("fill {}".format(bottles.pop(0)))
        elif bottles[0] == t:
            moves.append("discard {}".format(bottles.pop(0)))
        else:
            moves.append("transfer {} {}".format(bottles.pop(0), bottles.pop(0)))
        t -= bottles.pop(0)
    return "
".join(moves)

    black_balls = [stdin.readline().strip() for _ in range(N)]
    white_balls.sort()
    black_balls.sort()
    white_balls = [int(white_ball) for white_ball in white_balls]
    black_balls = [int(black_ball) for black_ball in black_balls]
    white_ball_index = 0
    black_ball_index = 0
    operations = 0
    while white_ball_index < N and black_ball_index < N:
        if white_balls[white_ball_index] < black_balls[black_ball_index]:
            white_ball_index += 1
        elif white_balls[white_ball_index] > black_balls[black_ball_index]:
            black_ball_index += 1
        else:
            white_ball_index += 1
            black_ball_index += 1
        operations += 1
    return str(operations)

def solution(stdin: str) -> str:
    n = int(stdin.readline().strip())
    a = [int(x) for x in stdin.readline().strip().split()]
    a.sort()
    a.reverse()
    p = 1
    q = 1
    for i in range(n):
        p *= a[i]
        q *= a[i]
    p = p % (10**9 + 7)
    q = q % (10**9 + 7)
    return str(p) + "/" + str(q)
